iversity Guide for Students","alternateName":"Road to Study in Turkey","publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/bioinformatics-egitimi-in-turkey.webp","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/bioinformatics-egitimi-in-turkey.webp","width":"2336","height":"1760","caption":"An image representing the field of bioinformatics, combining a DNA helix and a computer circuit","inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/turkey-bioinformatics-and-computational-biology/#webpage","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/turkey-bioinformatics-and-computational-biology/","name":"Turkish Bioinformatics and Computational Biology","datePublished":"2025-08-19T16:12:58+03:00","dateModified":"2026-03-15T21:46:25+03:00","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website"},"primaryImageOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/bioinformatics-egitimi-in-turkey.webp"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Person","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","caption":"Murat","inLanguage":"en-US"}},{"@type":"BlogPosting","headline":"Turkish Bioinformatics and Computational Biology","keywords":"Bioinformatics","datePublished":"2025-08-19T16:12:58+03:00","dateModified":"2026-03-15T21:46:25+03:00","articleSection":"University and Programs","author":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat"},"publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"description":"Where is bioinformatics education available in Turkey, what software language is required, what do graduates do? Learn and direct your career. Discover now!","name":"Turkish Bioinformatics and Computational Biology","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/turkey-bioinformatics-and-computational-biology/#richSnippet","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/turkey-bioinformatics-and-computational-biology/#webpage"},"image":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/bioinformatics-egitimi-in-turkey.webp"},"inLanguage":"en-US","mainEntityOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/turkey-bioinformatics-and-computational-biology/#webpage"}}]}]}'), '$.content_html', '<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The combination of genetics, artificial intelligence and data science has created a brand new field: bioinformatics. Analyses that used to be carried out only in laboratories are now solved with codes on computer screens. In Turkey, interest in this field has increased significantly in the last few years. Especially when biotechnology and health data management came to the agenda after the pandemic, universities started to open programs in this field rapidly. In this article, I have put together all the details for international students considering studying bioinformatics in Turkey.</p>


<div class="wp-block-spacer" style="height: 22px;" aria-hidden="true"> </div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" />
<div class="wp-block-spacer" style="height: 22px;" aria-hidden="true"> </div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="what-is-bioinformatics-and-why-is-it-important">What is bioinformatics and why is it important?</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Bioinformatics is an interdisciplinary field that combines computer science, mathematics and statistics to analyze biological data. It has a wide range of applications, such as finding the cause of genetic diseases, developing drugs or performing evolutionary analysis. The biggest reason for the increasing interest in this field in Turkey is the digitalization of the health sector.</p>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading">


<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Which universities have bioinformatics?</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>In rare cases, such as at Kadir Has University</strong>, there is a direct undergraduate education in bioinformatics and genetics.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>In universities such as Hacettepe University, Middle East Technical University (METU), Istanbul University and Gebze Technical University (GTU),</strong> there are field-specific, interdisciplinary master&#8217;s and doctoral programs under the relevant institutes.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Such as the <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/turkiyede-molekuler-biyoloji-ve-genetik/" data-type="post" data-id="1296">Department of Molecular Biology and Genetics</a> of Bosphorus University or the Biotechnology and Bioengineering program of Izmir Institute of Technology (IYTE), bioinformatics is included as a specialization or research area within the main department</p>


<figure class="wp-block-table">
<table class="has-fixed-layout">
<thead>
<tr>
<th>University</th>
<th>Program Type</th>
<th>Education Language</th>
<th>City</th>
</tr>
</thead>
