i">Türkiye&#8217;deki Başlıca AR-GE Üniversiteleri ve Enstitüleri</a><ol></ol></li><li class=""><a href="#ar-ge-projeleri-nelerdir-turkiyedeki-ornekler">AR-GE Projeleri Nelerdir? Türkiye’deki Örnekler</a><ol></ol></li><li class=""><a href="#turkiyenin-ar-ge-vizyonu-2030-yatirima-deger-mi">Türkiye’nin AR-GE Vizyonu 2030: Yatırıma Değer mi?</a><ol></ol></li><li class=""><a href="#simdi-sira-sende-turkiyede-ar-ge-hayaline-ilk-adimi-at">Şimdi Sıra Sende: Türkiye’de AR-GE Hayaline İlk Adımı At!</a></li></ol></nav></div>



<div style="height:55px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>



<h2 class=" wp-block-heading" id="turkiyede-ar-ge-nedir-ve-neden-onemlidir">Türkiye&#8217;de AR-GE Nedir ve Neden Önemlidir?</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">AR-GE yani Araştırma ve Geliştirme, sadece bilimsel deneyler yapmak değil; aynı zamanda teknoloji üretmek, inovasyon yaratmak ve ekonomik kalkınmaya yön vermek anlamına geliyor. Türkiye son yıllarda bu alana ciddi yatırım yapan ülkelerden biri. Özellikle savunma sanayi, yazılım, biyoteknoloji ve yeşil enerji gibi alanlarda öncü projelere imza atılıyor.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">2023 yılında Türkiye’nin AR-GE harcamaları Gayri Safi Yurtiçi Hasıla&#8217;nın yaklaşık %1,4&#8217;üne ulaştı ve bu oran artmaya devam ediyor (<a class="" href="https://www.tuik.gov.tr" target="_blank" rel="noopener">kaynak</a>). Devletin, özel sektörün ve üniversitelerin birlikte çalıştığı hibrit bir yapı var. Bu da uluslararası öğrenciler için büyük bir fırsat.</p>



<h3 class=" wp-block-heading" id="uluslararasi-ogrenciler-bu-surece-nasil-dahil-olur"><strong>Uluslararası Öğrenciler Bu Sürece Nasıl Dahil Olur?</strong></h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Türkiye’de eğitim almadan önce yapılması gereken en kritik şeylerden biri vize hazırlığını tamamlamaktır. Çünkü AR-GE projelerinde yer alabilmen için <strong>öğrenci vizesiyle yasal olarak Türkiye’ye giriş yapmış olman</strong> gerekir. Bu süreci kolaylaştırmak için şu yazılardan da faydalanabilirsin:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li class=""><a href="https://roadtostudy.com/">Türkiye&#8217;ye Gelmeden Önce Vize Hazırlıkları: Kontrol Listesi</a></li>



<li class=""><a href="https://roadtostudy.com/">Türkiye Vize Başvurusunda Sık Yapılan Hatalar ve Çözümleri</a></li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Her şey yolunda giderse, havalimanındaki işlemler sonrası öğrenci olarak ilk adımını Türkiye’de atmış oluyorsun.</p>



<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>



<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity"/>



<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>



<h3 class=" wp-block-heading" id="tubitak-ar-ge-calismalari-ve-1701-programi"><strong>TÜBİTAK AR-GE Çalışmaları ve 1701 Programı</strong></h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">TÜBİTAK (Türkiye Bilimsel ve Teknolojik Araştırma Kurumu), Türkiye’deki bilimsel AR-GE faaliyetlerinin en büyük destekçisi. Hem üniversitelere hem de öğrencilere projeler için fon sağlıyor.</p>



<h3 class=" wp-block-heading" id="tubitak-1701-programi-nedir"><strong>TÜBİTAK 1701 Programı Nedir?</strong></h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><a href="https://tubitak.gov.tr/tr/destekler/sanayi/ulusal-destek-programlari/1501-tubitak-sanayi-ar-ge-projeleri-destekleme-programi" target="_blank" rel="noopener">TÜBİTAK 1701, &#8220;Sanayi Ar-Ge Projeleri Destekleme Programı&#8221;</a> adıyla biliniyor. Özellikle üniversite-sanayi iş birliğini artırmayı hedefliyor. Bu program sayesinde öğrenciler gerçek hayattaki ürün geliştirme süreçlerine dahil olabiliyor.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Aşağıdaki tabloda TÜBİTAK 1701’e dair özet bilgileri bulabilirsin:</p>



<figure class="wp-block-table"><table class="has-fixed-layout"><thead><tr><th>Kriter</th><th>Bilgi</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Katılımcılar</td><td>Üniversiteler + Sanayi Kuruluşları</td></tr><tr><td>Destek Süresi</td><td>36 aya kadar</td></tr><tr><td>Başvuru Dönemi</td><td>Yıl boyunca açık çağrılar</td></tr><tr><td>Destek Tutarı</td><td>Projeye göre değişken, milyon TL seviyesinde</td></tr><tr><td>Uluslararası Katılım</td><td>Evet, Türkiye&#8217;de öğrenim gören öğrenciler dahil</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>



<h3 class=" wp-block-heading" id="uluslararasi-ogrenciler-icin-katilim"><strong>Uluslararası Öğrenciler için Katılım</strong></h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Eğer bir Türk üniversitesinde okuyorsan ve danışmanın TÜBİTAK projelerinde yer alıyorsa, sen de bu projelere asistan veya bursiyer olarak katılabilirsin. Bazı projelerde araştırma bursları sunuluyor. En güzeli de, bu burslar genellikle KYK veya Erasmus’tan daha yüksek olabiliyor.</p>



<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>



<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity"/>



<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>



<h3 class=" wp-block-heading" id="kosgeb-ve-ar-ge-destekleri-girisimciler-icin-firsatlar"><strong>KOSGEB ve AR-GE Destekleri: Girişimciler için Fırsatlar</strong></h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><a href="https://www.kosgeb.gov.tr/site/tr/genel/destekdetay/7664/arge-urge-ve-inovasyon-destek-programi" target="_blank" rel="noopener">KOSGEB (Küçük ve Orta Ölçekli İşletmeleri Geliştirme ve Destekleme İdaresi),</a> Türkiye’deki girişimcilere ve start-up’lara AR-GE desteği sağlayan bir diğer önemli kurum. Özellikle teknoloji tabanlı iş fikirlerini hayata geçirmek isteyen öğrenciler için büyük bir kaynak.</p>



<h3 class=" wp-block-heading" id="kosgeb-ar-ge-programlari-nedir"><strong>KOSGEB AR-GE Programları Nedir?</strong></h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">KOSGEB’in &#8220;Ar-Ge, Ür-Ge ve İnovasyon Destek Programı&#8221;, fikir aşamasından prototip üretimine kadar pek çok süreci kapsıyor. Yazılım geliştirme, mobil uygulama, yapay zeka veya biyoteknoloji alanında bir fikrin varsa, bu destek tam sana göre olabilir.</p>



<h3 class=" wp-block-heading" id="uluslararasi-ogrenciler-kosge-bden-nasil-yararlanabilir"><strong>Uluslararası Öğrenciler KOSGEB’den Nasıl Yararlanabilir?</strong></h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">KOSGEB doğrudan öğrencilere değil, Türkiye’de kayıtlı girişimlere destek veriyor. Ancak burada bir yol var: <strong>Bir Türk vatandaşını ortak olarak alarak şirket kurmak.</strong> Aşağıda adım adım nasıl ilerleyebileceğini listeledim:</p>



<ol class="wp-block-list">
<li class=""><strong>Bir Türk ortak ile şirket kur.</strong></li>



<li class=""><strong>Teknopark veya kuluçka merkezine başvur.</strong></li>



<li class=""><strong>İş planını hazırla ve KOSGEB’e sun.</strong></li>



<li class=""><strong>Destek alırsan, projeni hayata geçirmeye başla.</strong></li>
</ol>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Ayrıca bazı üniversitelerin teknoloji transfer ofisleri (TTO) bu süreçte sana ücretsiz danışmanlık da sağlıyor. Mesela <a class="" href="https://itucekirdek.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">İTÜ Çekirdek</a> bu konuda öncü.</p>



<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>



<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity"/>



<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>



<h2 class=" wp-block-heading" id="turkiyedeki-baslica-ar-ge-universiteleri-ve-enstituleri"><strong>Türkiye&#8217;deki Başlıca AR-GE Üniversiteleri ve Enstitüleri</strong></h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Eğer Türkiye’ye gelmeyi planlıyorsan, sadece diploma almak değil, aynı zamanda global ölçekte bir araştırma ortamının parçası olma şansın da var. Türkiye&#8217;de Araştırma ve Geliştirme&#8217;ye öncülük eden bazı üniversite ve enstitüler, dünya standartlarında çalışmalar yürütüyor.</p>



<h3 class=" wp-block-heading" id="odtu-itu-ve-bogazici-muhendislik-ve-bilim-usleri"><strong>ODTÜ, İTÜ ve Boğaziçi: Mühendislik ve Bilim Üsleri</strong></h3>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li class=""><strong>ODTÜ</strong> (Orta Doğu Teknik Üniversitesi): Bilim ve teknoloji alanındaki projeleriyle Avrupa’daki birçok üniversiteyle ortak çalışıyor.</li>



<li class=""><strong>İTÜ</strong> (İstanbul Teknik Üniversitesi): İTÜ ARI Teknokent sayesinde öğrenciler birçok sanayi projesine dahil olabiliyor.</li>



<li class=""><strong>Boğaziçi Üniversitesi</strong>: Enerji, yazılım ve çevre teknolojileri gibi alanlarda aktif projeler yürütüyor.</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Bu üniversitelerdeki AR-GE merkezleri sayesinde, öğrenciler araştırmalara doğrudan katkı sağlayabiliyor. Özellikle yüksek lisans ve doktora düzeyindeki öğrenciler için burslu pozisyonlar da mevcut.</p>



<h3 class=" wp-block-heading" id="tubitak-enstituleri-ve-arastirma-merkezleri"><strong>TÜBİTAK Enstitüleri ve Araştırma Merkezleri</strong></h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">TÜBİTAK’a bağlı enstitüler Türkiye genelinde yaygın. Örneğin:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li class=""><strong>Marmara Araştırma Merkezi (MAM)</strong> – Kimya, enerji ve genetik gibi alanlarda öncü.</li>



<li class=""><strong>BİLGEM</strong> – Siber güvenlik, yapay zeka ve büyük veri üzerinde çalışıyor.</li>



<li class=""><strong>UZAY Enstitüsü</strong> – Türkiye’nin uzay projelerinde aktif rol oynuyor.</li>
</ul>



<h3 class=" wp-block-heading" id="uluslararasi-ogrenciler-icin-katilim-rehberi"><strong>Uluslararası Öğrenciler için Katılım Rehberi</strong></h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Bir AR-GE projesinde yer alabilmen için Türkiye’de <strong>öğrenci ikamet izni</strong> alman şart. İlk girişten sonra belirli bir süre içinde Göç İdaresi’ne başvurmalısın. Bu aşamaları detaylı olarak öğrenmek istersen şu içerikler işine yarayabilir:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li class=""><a href="https://roadtostudy.com/">Türkiye&#8217;de Öğrenci İkamet İzni Yenileme Süreci</a></li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Proje süresince ikametini korumak da önemli. Her yıl yenilemen gereken bu iznin uzatma şartlarını ve olası hataları şu yazıda ele aldık:<br><a class="" href="#">Türkiye&#8217;de İkamet İzni Uzatma Başvurusunu Ne Zaman Yapmalı?</a></p>



<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>



<figure class="wp-block-table"><table class="has-fixed-layout"><thead><tr><th>Kurum / Merkez</th><th>Alanı</th><th>Katılım Yolu</th><th>Başvuru Linki</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>ODTÜ MEMS Merkezi</td><td>Mikro/Nano Sistemler</td><td>Lisansüstü öğrenci alımı</td><td><a href="https://www.metu.edu.tr/tr" target="_blank" rel="noopener">odtu.edu.tr</a></td></tr><tr><td>TÜBİTAK MAM</td><td>Enerji, Çevre, Biyo</td><td>Staj veya burslu pozisyonlar</td><td><a href="https://mam.tubitak.gov.tr/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">mam.tubitak.gov.tr</a></td></tr><tr><td>İTÜ ARI Teknokent</td><td>Girişimcilik, yazılım</td><td>Proje başvurusu / Staj</td><td><a href="https://ariteknokent.com.tr/tr" target="_blank" rel="noopener">ariteknokent.com.tr</a></td></tr></tbody></table></figure>



<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>



<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity"/>



<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>



<h2 class=" wp-block-heading" id="ar-ge-projeleri-nelerdir-turkiyedeki-ornekler">AR-GE Projeleri Nelerdir? Türkiye’deki Örnekler</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Türkiye&#8217;de her yıl yüzlerce farklı alanda AR-GE projesi yürütülüyor. Sağlık teknolojileri, savunma sanayi, yapay zeka, enerji sistemleri, tarım teknolojileri… Liste uzayıp gidiyor.</p>



<h3 class=" wp-block-heading" id="one-cikan-alanlar"><strong>Öne Çıkan Alanlar</strong></h3>



<ol class="wp-block-list">
<li class=""><strong>Savunma Sanayi</strong> – Bayraktar TB2 gibi İHA projeleri, ASELSAN ve ROKETSAN’ın öncülüğünde yürütülüyor.</li>



<li class=""><strong>Yazılım ve Yapay Zeka</strong> – Üniversitelerle birlikte yapılan ses tanıma, büyük veri ve otonom sistem çalışmaları.</li>



<li class=""><strong>Sağlık Teknolojileri</strong> – TÜBİTAK destekli yerli MR cihazı ve biyosensör projeleri.</li>



<li class=""><strong>Enerji</strong> – Yenilenebilir enerji kaynaklarına dair hidrojen ve güneş sistemleri üzerine AR-GE.</li>
</ol>



<h3 class=" wp-block-heading" id="ogrenciler-icin-acik-projeler"><strong>Öğrenciler İçin Açık Projeler</strong></h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Uluslararası öğrencilerin katılabileceği bazı programlar şunlar:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li class=""><strong>TÜBİTAK STAR Programı</strong> – Lisans ve yüksek lisans öğrencileri için burslu araştırma pozisyonları.</li>



<li class=""><strong>Sanayi Doktora Programı</strong> – Mezuniyet sonrası Türkiye’de kalmak isteyenler için.</li>



<li class=""><strong>TechAnkara Proje Pazarı</strong> – Öğrenciler fikirlerini doğrudan yatırımcılara sunabiliyor.</li>
</ul>



<h3 class=" wp-block-heading" id="projelerde-gonullu-veya-stajyer-olarak-yer-almak"><strong>Projelerde Gönüllü veya Stajyer Olarak Yer Almak</strong></h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Birçok laboratuvar, özellikle yaz döneminde gönüllü stajyer alıyor. Türkçe bilmek bazen bir avantaj ama bazı projeler İngilizce yürütülüyor. Tek yapman gereken doğru akademisyene ulaşmak. Mail atmak, özgeçmiş eklemek ve “Ben bu projeye neden katkı sağlamak istiyorum?” sorusuna içten bir yanıt vermek yeterli olabilir.</p>



<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>



<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity"/>



<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>



<h2 class=" wp-block-heading" id="turkiyenin-ar-ge-vizyonu-2030-yatirima-deger-mi">Türkiye’nin AR-GE Vizyonu 2030: Yatırıma Değer mi?</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Türkiye’nin “Milli Teknoloji Hamlesi” 2030 vizyonu, yalnızca kendi iç piyasasını değil, bölgesel ve küresel AR-GE merkezlerinden biri olmayı hedefliyor. Bu vizyon, uluslararası öğrenciler için hem araştırma hem de kariyer anlamında büyük kapılar açıyor.</p>



<h3 class=" wp-block-heading" id="ulusal-stratejiler-ve-uluslararasi-isbirlikleri"><strong>Ulusal Stratejiler ve Uluslararası İşbirlikleri</strong></h3>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li class="">Avrupa Birliği Ufuk 2020 ve 2030 programlarına aktif katılım</li>



<li class="">NATO ve CERN gibi kuruluşlarla işbirliği</li>



<li class="">Yurt dışındaki Türk akademisyenlerin geri dönüşünü sağlayan özel projeler</li>
</ul>



<h3 class=" wp-block-heading" id="mezuniyet-sonrasi-turkiyede-kalip-calisma-imkanlari"><strong>Mezuniyet Sonrası Türkiye’de Kalıp Çalışma İmkanları</strong></h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Türkiye’de yüksek lisans veya doktora yaptıysan, mezuniyet sonrası 1 yıl ikamet izni alabiliyorsun. Bu süreçte bir projeye dahil olabilir ya da girişim başlatabilirsin. Özellikle teknoparklar bu geçişte destek sunuyor.</p>



<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>



<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity"/>



<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>



<h2 class=" wp-block-heading" id="simdi-sira-sende-turkiyede-ar-ge-hayaline-ilk-adimi-at">Şimdi Sıra Sende: Türkiye’de AR-GE Hayaline İlk Adımı At!</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Gerçek bir araştırma deneyimi yaşamak, fikirlerini projeye dönüştürmek ve belki de dünyayı değiştirecek bir teknolojiye katkıda bulunmak istiyorsan, Türkiye seni bekliyor. Hem devlet destekli fonlar hem de üniversite-sanayi iş birlikleri sayesinde bu fırsatlara ulaşmak çok daha kolay hale geldi.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Road to Study</strong> olarak, sana en uygun AR-GE programını bulmana, başvuru belgelerini hazırlamana ve kabul sürecini kolaylaştırmana yardımcı olabiliriz.<br><a class="" href="https://roadtostudy.com">Şimdi bizimle iletişime geç</a> ve araştırma dolu bir geleceğe ilk adımını at!</p>', '$.wp_published_at', '2025-04-24T14:46:40Z', '$.wp_modified_at', '2026-03-15T18:56:36Z') WHERE "collection" = 'posts' AND "id" = ( SELECT "live_revision_id" FROM "ec_posts" WHERE "deleted_at" IS NULL AND "status" = 'published' AND "locale" = 'tr' AND "slug" = 'turkiye-ar-ge-programlari' );
UPDATE "ec_posts" SET "source_seo" = '{"title":"Undergraduate Conditions to Undergraduate Programs in Turkey","description":"Discover all the documents, dates and requirements required for undergraduate, graduate and doctoral applications in Turkey! Take action now with RoadToStudy.","robots":"follow, index, max-snippet:-1, max-video-preview:-1, max-image-preview:large","ogTitle":"Undergraduate Conditions to Undergraduate Programs in Turkey","ogDescription":"Discover all the documents, dates and requirements required for undergraduate, graduate and doctoral applications in Turkey! Take action now with RoadToStudy.","ogImage":"/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/undergraduate-requirement-study-turkey.webp","twitterCard":"summary_large_image","twitterTitle":"Undergraduate Conditions to Undergraduate Programs in Turkey","twitterDescription":"Discover all the documents, dates and requirements required for undergraduate, graduate and doctoral applications in Turkey! Take action now with RoadToStudy.","canonicalPath":"/en/undergraduate-requirement-study-turkey/","hreflang":[{"hreflang":"tr","href":"/turkiyede-lisans-basvurusu/"},{"hreflang":"en","href":"/en/undergraduate-requirement-study-turkey/"}],"jsonLd":[{"@context":"https://schema.org","@graph":[{"@type":["Organization","Person"],"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person","name":"Road to Study - Turkey University Guide for Students","url":"https://roadtostudy.com","logo":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#logo","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Kare-Logo-e1740739634958.png","contentUrl":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Kare-Logo-e1740739634958.png","caption":"Road to Study - Turkey University Guide for Students","inLanguage":"en-US","width":"450","height":"445"},"image":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#logo"}},{"@type":"WebSite","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website","url":"https://roadtostudy.com","name":"Road to Study - Turkey University Guide for Students","alternateName":"Road to Study in Turkey","publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/undergraduate-requirement-study-turkey.webp","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/undergraduate-requirement-study-turkey.webp","width":"1600","height":"1205","caption":"Infographic outlining undergraduate study requirements in Turkey, including exam process, deadlines, language scores, and required documents, with icons of students and universities.","inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/undergraduate-requirement-study-turkey/#webpage","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/undergraduate-requirement-study-turkey/","name":"Undergraduate Conditions to Undergraduate Programs in Turkey","datePublished":"2025-08-26T15:45:24+03:00","dateModified":"2026-03-15T21:44:51+03:00","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website"},"primaryImageOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/undergraduate-requirement-study-turkey.webp"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Person","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","caption":"Murat","inLanguage":"en-US"}},{"@type":"BlogPosting","headline":"Undergraduate Conditions to Undergraduate Programs in Turkey","keywords":"Undergraduate","datePublished":"2025-08-26T15:45:24+03:00","dateModified":"2026-03-15T21:44:51+03:00","articleSection":"University and Programs","author":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat"},"publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"description":"Discover all the documents, dates and requirements required for undergraduate, graduate and doctoral applications in Turkey! Take action now with RoadToStudy.","name":"Undergraduate Conditions to Undergraduate Programs in Turkey","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/undergraduate-requirement-study-turkey/#richSnippet","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/undergraduate-requirement-study-turkey/#webpage"},"image":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/undergraduate-requirement-study-turkey.webp"},"inLanguage":"en-US","mainEntityOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/undergraduate-requirement-study-turkey/#webpage"}}]}]}', "content_html" = '<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Admission requirements for undergraduate programs in Turkey vary between universities, but most institutions, especially for international students, follow a similar set of guidelines and require a common list of documents. The process typically involves an online application followed by in-person registration upon arrival.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">General Academic Requirements (bachelor&#8217;s degree)</h2>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>High School Diploma:</strong> You must have a high school diploma or be in your final year of high school. A provisional document stating your expected graduation date is usually accepted for the initial application.</li>



<li><strong>High School Transcripts:</strong> Official transcripts showing all courses taken and your grades are mandatory.</li>



<li><strong>Entrance Exam Scores:</strong> While some private universities may not require them, most public universities demand a score from a standardized test. The most common is the <strong>TR-YÖS</strong> (Turkish Exam for Foreign Students). Many universities also accept other international exams like the <strong>SAT</strong> or <strong>ACT</strong>. Minimum score requirements vary by university and program.</li>



<li><strong>Language Proficiency:</strong> If the program is taught in English, you will need to provide a score from a recognized English proficiency test like <strong>TOEFL</strong> (usually minimum 75 iBT) or <strong>PTE Academic</strong>. For programs taught in Turkish, you may need a <strong>TÖMER</strong> certificate (typically a C1 level). Students who don&#8217;t have a certificate may be required to take the university&#8217;s own proficiency exam or enroll in a preparatory language year.</li>
</ul>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Required Documents for Online Application</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">To complete your online application, you&#8217;ll need to prepare and upload digital copies of the following documents:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>High School Diploma:</strong> A copy of your diploma or a temporary graduation certificate.</li>



<li><strong>Official Transcripts:</strong> A copy of your high school academic transcripts.</li>



<li><strong>Passport:</strong> A clear photocopy of your valid passport&#8217;s photo and information page.</li>



<li><strong>Test Scores:</strong> Digital copies of your standardized test scores (e.g., TR-YÖS, SAT) and/or language proficiency test results.</li>



<li><strong>Photos:</strong> Passport-sized biometric photos.</li>



<li><strong>Motivation Letter:</strong> Some universities may require a statement of purpose or a motivation letter.</li>



<li><strong>Application Fee:</strong> Proof of payment for the non-refundable application fee.</li>
</ul>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Documents Required for Final Registration</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">After receiving your acceptance letter, you&#8217;ll need to bring the original documents to the university&#8217;s international office for final registration. These documents typically include:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Original High School Diploma and Transcripts:</strong> With a notarized Turkish or English translation if they are in another language.</li>



<li><strong>Equivalency Certificate (Denklik Belgesi):</strong> This is a crucial document obtained from a Turkish embassy or consulate abroad, or the Turkish Ministry of National Education, which certifies that your high school diploma is equivalent to a Turkish one.</li>



<li><strong>Student Visa:</strong> The student visa you obtained from a Turkish embassy or consulate in your home country.</li>



<li><strong>Health Insurance:</strong> Proof of a valid health insurance policy.</li>



<li><strong>Residence Permit:</strong> You will need to apply for a residence permit from local authorities after your arrival in Turkey, and you will need to provide the necessary documents for this process as well.</li>
</ul>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">How to apply for a university in Turkey?</h2>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">1. Choose a University and Program</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Turkey offers a wide range of public and private universities. Research different institutions and programs to find the best fit for your academic goals and career aspirations. Consider factors such as:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Program availability:</strong> Is your desired major offered?</li>



<li><strong>Language of instruction:</strong> Are you looking for a program in English or Turkish?</li>



<li><strong>Admission requirements:</strong> What are the specific GPA, test score, and document requirements?</li>



<li><strong>Tuition and scholarships:</strong> What are the costs, and what scholarship opportunities are available for international students?</li>
</ul>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">2. Check Admission Requirements</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Admission requirements can vary significantly between universities and programs, and between public and private institutions.</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Public Universities:</strong> Often have stricter requirements and may require scores from standardized tests. The most common is the <strong>TR-YÖS</strong>, a Turkish exam for international students. Some public universities also accept other international exams like the <strong>SAT</strong> or <strong>ACT</strong>.</li>



<li><strong>Private Universities:</strong> Generally have more flexible requirements, often placing a greater emphasis on your high school diploma grades and transcripts. They may also consider scores from international exams like the SAT, but it is not always mandatory.</li>
</ul>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">3. Prepare Your Documents</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The documents required for your initial online application typically include:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>High School Diploma:</strong> A copy of your high school diploma.  If you have not yet graduated, you can submit an official document stating your expected graduation date.</li>



<li><strong>Official Transcripts:</strong> High school transcripts showing all courses and grades.</li>



<li><strong>Valid Identification:</strong> A copy of your passport or national ID card.</li>



<li><strong>Language Proficiency Certificate:</strong> If applying for an English-taught program, you may need a <strong>TOEFL</strong> or <strong>PTE</strong> certificate. For Turkish-taught programs, a <strong>TÖMER</strong> certificate is often required. If you don&#8217;t have one, many universities offer their own proficiency test.</li>



<li><strong>Standardized Test Scores (if applicable):</strong> Copies of your test scores (e.g., SAT, ACT, TR-YÖS).</li>



<li><strong>Passport-Sized Photos:</strong> Digital copies of recent photos.</li>



<li><strong>Statement of Purpose/Motivation Letter:</strong> A personal essay explaining your reasons for applying to the university and program.</li>



<li><strong>Application Fee Receipt:</strong> Proof of payment for the non-refundable application fee.</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Note:</strong> All documents not in English or Turkish must be accompanied by a notarized translation.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">4. Meet Application Deadlines</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Application deadlines for Turkish universities are set by each institution and can vary. Most universities have a fall intake with deadlines typically ranging from <strong>May to August</strong>. For highly competitive programs or scholarships, the deadlines might be much earlier. It is crucial to check the specific dates on the university&#8217;s official website and submit your application well in advance.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">5. Submit Your Application</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Once you have gathered all the necessary documents, you will submit them through the university&#8217;s online application portal. Some universities may also require you to send physical copies of your documents via post.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">6. Post-Acceptance Process</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">If your application is successful, you will receive a conditional or final acceptance letter. This is a crucial document for the next steps.</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Student Visa:</strong> You will need to apply for a <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/en/student-visa-application-process/" data-type="post" data-id="6685">student visa</a> at the nearest Turkish embassy or consulate in your home country. The acceptance letter from the university is a mandatory document for this process.</li>



<li><strong>Equivalency Certificate:</strong> Before final registration at the university, you must obtain a <strong>&#8220;Denklik Belgesi&#8221;</strong> (High School Equivalency Certificate) from a Turkish embassy or the Ministry of National Education in Turkey. This document verifies that your high school diploma is equivalent to a Turkish one.</li>



<li><strong>Final Registration:</strong> Upon arrival in Turkey, you will need to complete your final registration at the university by providing original copies of all your documents.</li>



<li><strong>Residence Permit:</strong> As an international student, you must apply for a residence permit from the local authorities within one month of your arrival.</li>
</ul>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">frequently asked questions</h2>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">What is the cheapest university in Turkey for international students?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The cheapest universities for international students are generally public universities, where annual tuition fees can be under $1000 USD. The exact cost varies depending on the specific university and the program you choose.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">What is the required percentage to study in Turkey?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">There is no specific percentage required to study in Turkey. Instead, universities and programs have minimum grade point averages (GPA) or standardized test score requirements. These can differ significantly depending on the field of study.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">What is the entrance exam for university in Turkey?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The most common university entrance exam for international students in Turkey is the <strong>TR-YÖS</strong> (Turkish Exam for Foreign Students). Some universities also accept internationally recognized exams like the <strong>SAT</strong> or <strong>ACT</strong>.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">How long is an undergraduate in Turkey?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Most bachelor&#8217;s degrees in Turkey take <strong>four years</strong> to complete. However, some professional programs like medicine take <strong>six years</strong>, dentistry and veterinary medicine take <strong>five years</strong>, and pharmacy takes <strong>five years</strong>.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">What is a bachelor&#8217;s degree in Turkey?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">A bachelor&#8217;s degree in Turkey is known as a <strong>&#8220;Lisans Diploması.&#8221;</strong> It is a first-cycle higher education qualification awarded after completing a program that typically lasts four years and involves a minimum of 240 ECTS credits.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Is Turkey good for bachelors?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Yes, Turkey is a popular choice for a bachelor&#8217;s degree due to its <strong>high-quality education</strong>, diverse range of programs in both English and Turkish, and a vibrant, multicultural environment. It also offers relatively <strong>affordable tuition fees</strong> and a lower cost of living compared to many European countries.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">How much does a bachelor&#8217;s degree cost in Turkey?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The cost of a bachelor&#8217;s degree in Turkey varies significantly. For international students, <strong>public university</strong> tuition can range from <strong>$100 to $4,000 USD</strong> per year, depending on the program. <strong>Private universities</strong> are more expensive, with fees starting at around <strong>$5,000 USD</strong> and reaching over <strong>$20,000 USD</strong> annually for certain fields like medicine.</p>', "wp_published_at" = '2025-08-26T12:45:24Z', "wp_modified_at" = '2026-03-15T18:44:51Z', "featured_image" = '{"provider":"external","src":"/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/undergraduate-requirement-study-turkey.webp","alt":"Infographic outlining undergraduate study requirements in Turkey, including exam process, deadlines, language scores, and required documents, with icons of students and universities.","title":"undergraduate-requirement-study-turkey"}' WHERE "deleted_at" IS NULL AND "status" = 'published' AND "locale" = 'en' AND "slug" = 'undergraduate-requirement-study-turkey';
UPDATE "revisions" SET "data" = json_set("data", '$.source_seo', json('{"title":"Undergraduate Conditions to Undergraduate Programs in Turkey","description":"Discover all the documents, dates and requirements required for undergraduate, graduate and doctoral applications in Turkey! Take action now with RoadToStudy.","robots":"follow, index, max-snippet:-1, max-video-preview:-1, max-image-preview:large","ogTitle":"Undergraduate Conditions to Undergraduate Programs in Turkey","ogDescription":"Discover all the documents, dates and requirements required for undergraduate, graduate and doctoral applications in Turkey! Take action now with RoadToStudy.","ogImage":"/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/undergraduate-requirement-study-turkey.webp","twitterCard":"summary_large_image","twitterTitle":"Undergraduate Conditions to Undergraduate Programs in Turkey","twitterDescription":"Discover all the documents, dates and requirements required for undergraduate, graduate and doctoral applications in Turkey! Take action now with RoadToStudy.","canonicalPath":"/en/undergraduate-requirement-study-turkey/","hreflang":[{"hreflang":"tr","href":"/turkiyede-lisans-basvurusu/"},{"hreflang":"en","href":"/en/undergraduate-requirement-study-turkey/"}],"jsonLd":[{"@context":"https://schema.org","@graph":[{"@type":["Organization","Person"],"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person","name":"Road to Study - Turkey University Guide for Students","url":"https://roadtostudy.com","logo":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#logo","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Kare-Logo-e1740739634958.png","contentUrl":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Kare-Logo-e1740739634958.png","caption":"Road to Study - Turkey University Guide for Students","inLanguage":"en-US","width":"450","height":"445"},"image":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#logo"}},{"@type":"WebSite","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website","url":"https://roadtostudy.com","name":"Road to Study - Turkey University Guide for Students","alternateName":"Road to Study in Turkey","publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/undergraduate-requirement-study-turkey.webp","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/undergraduate-requirement-study-turkey.webp","width":"1600","height":"1205","caption":"Infographic outlining undergraduate study requirements in Turkey, including exam process, deadlines, language scores, and required documents, with icons of students and universities.","inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/undergraduate-requirement-study-turkey/#webpage","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/undergraduate-requirement-study-turkey/","name":"Undergraduate Conditions to Undergraduate Programs in Turkey","datePublished":"2025-08-26T15:45:24+03:00","dateModified":"2026-03-15T21:44:51+03:00","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website"},"primaryImageOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/undergraduate-requirement-study-turkey.webp"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Person","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","caption":"Murat","inLanguage":"en-US"}},{"@type":"BlogPosting","headline":"Undergraduate Conditions to Undergraduate Programs in Turkey","keywords":"Undergraduate","datePublished":"2025-08-26T15:45:24+03:00","dateModified":"2026-03-15T21:44:51+03:00","articleSection":"University and Programs","author":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat"},"publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"description":"Discover all the documents, dates and requirements required for undergraduate, graduate and doctoral applications in Turkey! Take action now with RoadToStudy.","name":"Undergraduate Conditions to Undergraduate Programs in Turkey","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/undergraduate-requirement-study-turkey/#richSnippet","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/undergraduate-requirement-study-turkey/#webpage"},"image":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/undergraduate-requirement-study-turkey.webp"},"inLanguage":"en-US","mainEntityOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/undergraduate-requirement-study-turkey/#webpage"}}]}]}'), '$.content_html', '<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Admission requirements for undergraduate programs in Turkey vary between universities, but most institutions, especially for international students, follow a similar set of guidelines and require a common list of documents. The process typically involves an online application followed by in-person registration upon arrival.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">General Academic Requirements (bachelor&#8217;s degree)</h2>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>High School Diploma:</strong> You must have a high school diploma or be in your final year of high school. A provisional document stating your expected graduation date is usually accepted for the initial application.</li>



<li><strong>High School Transcripts:</strong> Official transcripts showing all courses taken and your grades are mandatory.</li>



<li><strong>Entrance Exam Scores:</strong> While some private universities may not require them, most public universities demand a score from a standardized test. The most common is the <strong>TR-YÖS</strong> (Turkish Exam for Foreign Students). Many universities also accept other international exams like the <strong>SAT</strong> or <strong>ACT</strong>. Minimum score requirements vary by university and program.</li>



<li><strong>Language Proficiency:</strong> If the program is taught in English, you will need to provide a score from a recognized English proficiency test like <strong>TOEFL</strong> (usually minimum 75 iBT) or <strong>PTE Academic</strong>. For programs taught in Turkish, you may need a <strong>TÖMER</strong> certificate (typically a C1 level). Students who don&#8217;t have a certificate may be required to take the university&#8217;s own proficiency exam or enroll in a preparatory language year.</li>
</ul>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Required Documents for Online Application</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">To complete your online application, you&#8217;ll need to prepare and upload digital copies of the following documents:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>High School Diploma:</strong> A copy of your diploma or a temporary graduation certificate.</li>



<li><strong>Official Transcripts:</strong> A copy of your high school academic transcripts.</li>



<li><strong>Passport:</strong> A clear photocopy of your valid passport&#8217;s photo and information page.</li>



<li><strong>Test Scores:</strong> Digital copies of your standardized test scores (e.g., TR-YÖS, SAT) and/or language proficiency test results.</li>



<li><strong>Photos:</strong> Passport-sized biometric photos.</li>



<li><strong>Motivation Letter:</strong> Some universities may require a statement of purpose or a motivation letter.</li>



<li><strong>Application Fee:</strong> Proof of payment for the non-refundable application fee.</li>
</ul>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Documents Required for Final Registration</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">After receiving your acceptance letter, you&#8217;ll need to bring the original documents to the university&#8217;s international office for final registration. These documents typically include:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Original High School Diploma and Transcripts:</strong> With a notarized Turkish or English translation if they are in another language.</li>



<li><strong>Equivalency Certificate (Denklik Belgesi):</strong> This is a crucial document obtained from a Turkish embassy or consulate abroad, or the Turkish Ministry of National Education, which certifies that your high school diploma is equivalent to a Turkish one.</li>



<li><strong>Student Visa:</strong> The student visa you obtained from a Turkish embassy or consulate in your home country.</li>



<li><strong>Health Insurance:</strong> Proof of a valid health insurance policy.</li>



<li><strong>Residence Permit:</strong> You will need to apply for a residence permit from local authorities after your arrival in Turkey, and you will need to provide the necessary documents for this process as well.</li>
</ul>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">How to apply for a university in Turkey?</h2>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">1. Choose a University and Program</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Turkey offers a wide range of public and private universities. Research different institutions and programs to find the best fit for your academic goals and career aspirations. Consider factors such as:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Program availability:</strong> Is your desired major offered?</li>



<li><strong>Language of instruction:</strong> Are you looking for a program in English or Turkish?</li>



<li><strong>Admission requirements:</strong> What are the specific GPA, test score, and document requirements?</li>



<li><strong>Tuition and scholarships:</strong> What are the costs, and what scholarship opportunities are available for international students?</li>
</ul>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">2. Check Admission Requirements</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Admission requirements can vary significantly between universities and programs, and between public and private institutions.</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Public Universities:</strong> Often have stricter requirements and may require scores from standardized tests. The most common is the <strong>TR-YÖS</strong>, a Turkish exam for international students. Some public universities also accept other international exams like the <strong>SAT</strong> or <strong>ACT</strong>.</li>



<li><strong>Private Universities:</strong> Generally have more flexible requirements, often placing a greater emphasis on your high school diploma grades and transcripts. They may also consider scores from international exams like the SAT, but it is not always mandatory.</li>
</ul>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">3. Prepare Your Documents</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The documents required for your initial online application typically include:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>High School Diploma:</strong> A copy of your high school diploma.  If you have not yet graduated, you can submit an official document stating your expected graduation date.</li>



<li><strong>Official Transcripts:</strong> High school transcripts showing all courses and grades.</li>



<li><strong>Valid Identification:</strong> A copy of your passport or national ID card.</li>



<li><strong>Language Proficiency Certificate:</strong> If applying for an English-taught program, you may need a <strong>TOEFL</strong> or <strong>PTE</strong> certificate. For Turkish-taught programs, a <strong>TÖMER</strong> certificate is often required. If you don&#8217;t have one, many universities offer their own proficiency test.</li>



<li><strong>Standardized Test Scores (if applicable):</strong> Copies of your test scores (e.g., SAT, ACT, TR-YÖS).</li>



<li><strong>Passport-Sized Photos:</strong> Digital copies of recent photos.</li>



<li><strong>Statement of Purpose/Motivation Letter:</strong> A personal essay explaining your reasons for applying to the university and program.</li>



<li><strong>Application Fee Receipt:</strong> Proof of payment for the non-refundable application fee.</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Note:</strong> All documents not in English or Turkish must be accompanied by a notarized translation.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">4. Meet Application Deadlines</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Application deadlines for Turkish universities are set by each institution and can vary. Most universities have a fall intake with deadlines typically ranging from <strong>May to August</strong>. For highly competitive programs or scholarships, the deadlines might be much earlier. It is crucial to check the specific dates on the university&#8217;s official website and submit your application well in advance.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">5. Submit Your Application</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Once you have gathered all the necessary documents, you will submit them through the university&#8217;s online application portal. Some universities may also require you to send physical copies of your documents via post.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">6. Post-Acceptance Process</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">If your application is successful, you will receive a conditional or final acceptance letter. This is a crucial document for the next steps.</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Student Visa:</strong> You will need to apply for a <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/en/student-visa-application-process/" data-type="post" data-id="6685">student visa</a> at the nearest Turkish embassy or consulate in your home country. The acceptance letter from the university is a mandatory document for this process.</li>



<li><strong>Equivalency Certificate:</strong> Before final registration at the university, you must obtain a <strong>&#8220;Denklik Belgesi&#8221;</strong> (High School Equivalency Certificate) from a Turkish embassy or the Ministry of National Education in Turkey. This document verifies that your high school diploma is equivalent to a Turkish one.</li>



<li><strong>Final Registration:</strong> Upon arrival in Turkey, you will need to complete your final registration at the university by providing original copies of all your documents.</li>



<li><strong>Residence Permit:</strong> As an international student, you must apply for a residence permit from the local authorities within one month of your arrival.</li>
</ul>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">frequently asked questions</h2>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">What is the cheapest university in Turkey for international students?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The cheapest universities for international students are generally public universities, where annual tuition fees can be under $1000 USD. The exact cost varies depending on the specific university and the program you choose.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">What is the required percentage to study in Turkey?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">There is no specific percentage required to study in Turkey. Instead, universities and programs have minimum grade point averages (GPA) or standardized test score requirements. These can differ significantly depending on the field of study.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">What is the entrance exam for university in Turkey?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The most common university entrance exam for international students in Turkey is the <strong>TR-YÖS</strong> (Turkish Exam for Foreign Students). Some universities also accept internationally recognized exams like the <strong>SAT</strong> or <strong>ACT</strong>.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">How long is an undergraduate in Turkey?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Most bachelor&#8217;s degrees in Turkey take <strong>four years</strong> to complete. However, some professional programs like medicine take <strong>six years</strong>, dentistry and veterinary medicine take <strong>five years</strong>, and pharmacy takes <strong>five years</strong>.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">What is a bachelor&#8217;s degree in Turkey?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">A bachelor&#8217;s degree in Turkey is known as a <strong>&#8220;Lisans Diploması.&#8221;</strong> It is a first-cycle higher education qualification awarded after completing a program that typically lasts four years and involves a minimum of 240 ECTS credits.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Is Turkey good for bachelors?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Yes, Turkey is a popular choice for a bachelor&#8217;s degree due to its <strong>high-quality education</strong>, diverse range of programs in both English and Turkish, and a vibrant, multicultural environment. It also offers relatively <strong>affordable tuition fees</strong> and a lower cost of living compared to many European countries.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">How much does a bachelor&#8217;s degree cost in Turkey?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The cost of a bachelor&#8217;s degree in Turkey varies significantly. For international students, <strong>public university</strong> tuition can range from <strong>$100 to $4,000 USD</strong> per year, depending on the program. <strong>Private universities</strong> are more expensive, with fees starting at around <strong>$5,000 USD</strong> and reaching over <strong>$20,000 USD</strong> annually for certain fields like medicine.</p>', '$.wp_published_at', '2025-08-26T12:45:24Z', '$.wp_modified_at', '2026-03-15T18:44:51Z', '$.featured_image', json('{"provider":"external","src":"/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/undergraduate-requirement-study-turkey.webp","alt":"Infographic outlining undergraduate study requirements in Turkey, including exam process, deadlines, language scores, and required documents, with icons of students and universities.","title":"undergraduate-requirement-study-turkey"}')) WHERE "collection" = 'posts' AND "id" = ( SELECT "live_revision_id" FROM "ec_posts" WHERE "deleted_at" IS NULL AND "status" = 'published' AND "locale" = 'en' AND "slug" = 'undergraduate-requirement-study-turkey' );
UPDATE "ec_posts" SET "source_seo" = '{"title":"Türkiye’de Lisans Başvurusu 2025: 6 Adımda Rehber","description":"Türkiye’de lisans, yüksek lisans ve doktora başvurusu için gereken tüm belgeleri, tarihleri ve şartları keşfet! RoadToStudy ile hemen harekete geç.","robots":"follow, index, max-snippet:-1, max-video-preview:-1, max-image-preview:large","ogTitle":"Türkiye’de Lisans Başvurusu 2025: 6 Adımda Rehber","ogDescription":"Türkiye’de lisans, yüksek lisans ve doktora başvurusu için gereken tüm belgeleri, tarihleri ve şartları keşfet! RoadToStudy ile hemen harekete geç.","ogImage":"/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/undergraduate-requirement-study-turkey.webp","twitterCard":"summary_large_image","twitterTitle":"Türkiye’de Lisans Başvurusu 2025: 6 Adımda Rehber","twitterDescription":"Türkiye’de lisans, yüksek lisans ve doktora başvurusu için gereken tüm belgeleri, tarihleri ve şartları keşfet! RoadToStudy ile hemen harekete geç.","canonicalPath":"/turkiyede-lisans-basvurusu/","hreflang":[{"hreflang":"tr","href":"/turkiyede-lisans-basvurusu/"},{"hreflang":"en","href":"/en/undergraduate-requirement-study-turkey/"}],"jsonLd":[{"@context":"https://schema.org","@graph":[{"@type":["Organization","Person"],"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person","name":"Road to Study - Turkey University Guide for Students","url":"https://roadtostudy.com","logo":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#logo","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Kare-Logo-e1740739634958.png","contentUrl":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Kare-Logo-e1740739634958.png","caption":"Road to Study - Turkey University Guide for Students","inLanguage":"tr","width":"450","height":"445"},"image":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#logo"}},{"@type":"WebSite","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website","url":"https://roadtostudy.com","name":"Road to Study - Turkey University Guide for Students","alternateName":"Road to Study in Turkey","publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"inLanguage":"tr"},{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/undergraduate-requirement-study-turkey.webp","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/undergraduate-requirement-study-turkey.webp","width":"1600","height":"1205","inLanguage":"tr"},{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/turkiyede-lisans-basvurusu/#webpage","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/turkiyede-lisans-basvurusu/","name":"Türkiye’de Lisans Başvurusu 2025: 6 Adımda Rehber","datePublished":"2025-04-25T07:19:40+03:00","dateModified":"2026-03-15T21:56:34+03:00","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website"},"primaryImageOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/undergraduate-requirement-study-turkey.webp"},"inLanguage":"tr"},{"@type":"Person","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/author/murat/","name":"Murat","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/author/murat/","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","caption":"Murat","inLanguage":"tr"}},{"@type":"BlogPosting","headline":"Türkiye’de Lisans Başvurusu 2025: 6 Adımda Rehber","keywords":"türkiye''de lisans","datePublished":"2025-04-25T07:19:40+03:00","dateModified":"2026-03-15T21:56:34+03:00","articleSection":"Üniversite ve Programlar","author":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/author/murat/","name":"Murat"},"publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"description":"Türkiye’de lisans, yüksek lisans ve doktora başvurusu için gereken tüm belgeleri, tarihleri ve şartları keşfet! RoadToStudy ile hemen harekete geç.","name":"Türkiye’de Lisans Başvurusu 2025: 6 Adımda Rehber","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/turkiyede-lisans-basvurusu/#richSnippet","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/turkiyede-lisans-basvurusu/#webpage"},"image":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/undergraduate-requirement-study-turkey.webp"},"inLanguage":"tr","mainEntityOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/turkiyede-lisans-basvurusu/#webpage"}}]}]}', "content_html" = '<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Türkiye&#8217;de lisans programına geçiş süreci, ÖSYM tarafından yönetilen merkezi bir sistem olan Yükseköğretim Kurumları Sınavı (YKS) ile gerçekleşir. 2017-2018 eğitim-öğretim yılından bu yana uygulanan bu sistem , adayların akademik yeterliliklerini, alan bilgilerini ve dil becerilerini ölçen çok aşamalı bir yapıya sahiptir. Bu rapor, sadece YKS sürecini değil, aynı zamanda yabancı uyruklu öğrenci başvurularını ve alternatif yolları da ele alarak, adaylara stratejik bir bakış açısı sunmayı amaçlamaktadır.  </p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Yükseköğretim Kurumları Sınavı (YKS) Sistemi ve Oturumları</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">YKS, öğrencilerin akademik yetkinliklerini değerlendirmek için tasarlanmış ve genellikle üç oturumdan oluşan bir sınavdır. &nbsp;</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>1.1. Temel Yeterlilik Testi (TYT)</strong></p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">TYT, YKS&#8217;nin ilk ve tüm adaylar için zorunlu olan oturumudur. Sınavın temel amacı, adayların lise eğitiminin ilk iki yılında (9. ve 10. sınıflar) edindikleri bilgi ve temel yeterlilikleri ölçmektir. Toplam 120 sorudan oluşan bu test , 165 dakikalık süresiyle öğrencilerin okuduğunu anlama, yorumlama ve temel matematiksel işlemleri yapma yeteneklerini değerlendirir. Soru dağılımı şu şekildedir: Türkçe 40, Matematik 40 (yaklaşık 10&#8217;u Geometri), Sosyal Bilimler 20 ve Fen Bilimleri 20 sorudur. Bu test, yükseköğretime geçişte ilk eleme basamağı olma özelliği taşır. &nbsp;</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>1.2. Alan Yeterlilik Testleri (AYT)</strong></p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">AYT, YKS&#8217;nin ikinci oturumudur ve dört yıllık lisans programlarına yerleşmek isteyenler için en kritik adımdır. TYT&#8217;nin aksine, AYT lise müfredatının 11. ve 12. sınıflarındaki konulara odaklanır ve toplam YKS puanının yüzde 60&#8217;ını oluşturur. Sınavda yer alan testler ve soru sayıları, adayların tercih ettikleri puan türüne göre şekillenir: Matematik 40, Fen Bilimleri 40, Türk Dili ve Edebiyatı-Sosyal Bilimler-1 40, Sosyal Bilimler-2 40 sorudan oluşmaktadır. AYT, yüksek bir performansla orta düzeydeki bir TYT sonucunu telafi edebilecek güce sahip olduğu için, adayların bu oturuma özel olarak odaklanması önemlidir. &nbsp;</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>1.3. Yabancı Dil Testi (YDT)</strong></p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">YDT, YKS&#8217;nin dil puanıyla öğrenci kabul eden bölümlerine girmek isteyen adaylar için üçüncü oturumdur. Almanca, Arapça, Fransızca, İngilizce veya Rusça dillerinden birini seçebileceğiniz bu sınav, 80 sorudan oluşur ve 120 dakika sürer. YDT&#8217;ye katılan adayların da TYT&#8217;den bir puan alması gerekmektedir, bu da dil yetkinliğinin temel akademik yeterliliklerle birlikte değerlendirildiğini gösterir. &nbsp;</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>YKS Başvuru Süreci ve Resmi Takvim Analizi</strong></p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">YKS&#8217;ye başvuru süreci, dikkatli takip gerektiren planlı bir süreçtir.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>2.1. YKS Başvuru Adımları</strong></p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">YKS başvuruları,<a href="https://ais.osym.gov.tr/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"> ÖSYM&#8217;nin resmi sitesi</a> üzerinden Aday İşlemleri Sistemi&#8217;ne (AİS) giriş yapılarak gerçekleştirilir. Daha önce ÖSYM sınavlarına başvurmamış adaylar, e-Devlet şifreleri ile kolayca kayıt olabilirler. Başvuru adımları genel olarak sınav tarihlerini takip etmek, AİS&#8217;e giriş yapmak, başvuru formunu doldurmak ve sınav ücretini yatırmak şeklinde ilerler. Ücretin yatırılmaması başvurunun geçersiz sayılmasına neden olur.  </p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>2.2. Resmi ve Tahmini Sınav Takvimi Analizi</strong></p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">YKS&#8217;nin kesin tarihleri her yıl ÖSYM tarafından duyurulur. Geçmiş yıllarda olduğu gibi, 2024 YKS 8-9 Haziran&#8217;da , 2025 YKS ise 21-22 Haziran&#8217;da yapılmıştır. Ancak, 2026 sınav takvimi gibi geleceğe yönelik tahminlerde kaynaklar arasında farklılıklar görülebilmektedir. Bu durum, adayların yanlış bilgilere karşı dikkatli olmalarını ve en güncel ve doğru bilgi için her zaman ÖSYM&#8217;nin resmi internet sitesini kontrol etmelerini zorunlu kılmaktadır. &nbsp;</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Puan ve Sıralama Analizi: Stratejik Bir Yaklaşım</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Sınav başarısı, sadece elde edilen bir puandan ibaret değildir. Stratejik bir tercih listesi oluşturmak için puan ve başarı sıralaması arasındaki ilişkiyi anlamak gerekir.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>3.1. Puan Hesaplama Mekanizması</strong></p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">YKS&#8217;de puanlar, her 4 yanlışın 1 doğruyu götürdüğü net hesaplama formülüne göre belirlenir. Bu netlerden elde edilen ham puana, lise diploma notunun 0.12 ile çarpılmasıyla hesaplanan Ortaöğretim Başarı Puanı (OBP) eklenerek yerleştirme puanı oluşturulur. OBP, yerleştirme puanına en fazla 60 puan katkı sağlar. Toplam YKS puanı ise, TYT&#8217;nin %40 ve AYT/YDT&#8217;nin %60 ağırlıkla hesaplanmasıyla belirlenir. &nbsp;</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>3.2. Başarı Sıralamasının Önemi</strong></p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Tercih döneminde puanlardan ziyade başarı sıralamasına odaklanmak çok daha önemlidir. Çünkü puanlar, sınavın zorluğuna ve aday sayısına göre her yıl değişirken, başarı sıralaması daha tutarlı bir göstergedir. YÖK, bazı popüler bölümler için başarı sıralaması eşikleri belirlemektedir: Hukuk için en düşük 125.000 , Mühendislik için yaklaşık 120.000 ve Tıp için yaklaşık 50.000 sıralama eşiği bulunur. Aşağıdaki tablo, bu bölümlerdeki rekabeti gözler önüne sermektedir. YÖK Atlas gibi resmi araçlar, bu sıralamaları analiz etmek için en doğru kaynaktır. &nbsp;</p>



