#person"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/international-students-in-turkey.webp","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/international-students-in-turkey.webp","width":"1152","height":"864","caption":"Social life for international students studying at universities in Turkey.","inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/programs-post-graduation-employment-rates/#webpage","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/programs-post-graduation-employment-rates/","name":"Programs &amp; Post-Graduation Employment Rates in Turkey","datePublished":"2026-02-24T10:39:50+03:00","dateModified":"2026-03-15T21:39:05+03:00","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website"},"primaryImageOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/international-students-in-turkey.webp"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Person","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","caption":"Murat","inLanguage":"en-US"}},{"@type":"BlogPosting","headline":"Programs &amp; Post-Graduation Employment Rates in Turkey","keywords":"Post-Graduation,Popular Programs","datePublished":"2026-02-24T10:39:50+03:00","dateModified":"2026-03-15T21:39:05+03:00","articleSection":"University and Programs","author":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat"},"publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"description":"Discover technology and innovation trends in education in Turkey! Take a step toward the future of education today. Learn now!","name":"Programs &amp; Post-Graduation Employment Rates in Turkey","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/programs-post-graduation-employment-rates/#richSnippet","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/programs-post-graduation-employment-rates/#webpage"},"image":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/international-students-in-turkey.webp"},"inLanguage":"en-US","mainEntityOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/programs-post-graduation-employment-rates/#webpage"}}]}]}'), '$.content_html', '<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Employment in Turkey offers a culturally rich experience and significant opportunities for a career after graduation. Of course, in order to take advantage of these opportunities, it is necessary to choose the right program and analyze the trends in the business world well. I have compiled all the important points for you, starting from the popular majors in Turkey to the labor force data and job finding processes in 2025. <strong>Let&#8217;s get started!</strong></p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="popular-programs-and-study-periods-in-turkey">Popular Programs and Study Periods in Turkey</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Unlike many other parts of the world, university education in Turkey is offered at both state and foundation (private) universities. Although the language of instruction is mostly Turkish, English programs are also quite common. English-language engineering, medicine, business and social sciences programs for international students are particularly popular.</p>


<h3 id="turkiyede-en-cok-ctercih-edilen- lisans-ve-yuksek-lisans-bolumleri" class="wp-block-heading"><strong>The Most Preferred Undergraduate and Graduate Programs in Turkey</strong></h3>


<p class="wp-block-paragraph">According to the latest data of OSYM, the most preferred departments among local and foreign students in Turkey are as follows:</p>


<figure class="wp-block-table">
<table class="has-fixed-layout">
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Department</th>
<th>Graduate Program Popularity Rank</th>
<th>Average Time to Find a Job After Graduation</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<thead>
<tr>
<td>Computer Engineering</td>
<td>1st</td>
<td>6-8 months</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Medicine</td>
<td>2. ranked</td>
<td>2-3 months</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Business</td>
<td>3rd</td>
<td>8-10 months</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Electrical and Electronics Engineering</td>
<td>4th</td>
<td>7-9 months</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Psychology</td>
<td>5th</td>
<td>9-12 months</td>
</tr>
</thead>
</table>
</figure>


<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Source: <a href="https://www.yok.gov.tr/Sayfalar/Haberler/2024/2024-universite-izleme-ve-degerlendirme-genel-raporu-yayimlandi.aspx" target="_blank" rel="noopener">YÖK Atlas 2024 Data</a></p>


<h3 id="egitim-sureleri-ve-program-turlerine-gore-farkliliklar" class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Differences in Education Duration and Program Types</strong></h3>


<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Turkey&#8217;s education periods are generally as follows:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Undergraduate: 4 years (Engineering, Economics, Law, etc.)</li>



<li>Master&#8217;s Degree: 2 years</li>



<li>Medical Faculty: 6 years</li>



<li>Dentistry and Pharmacy: 5 years</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">In addition, students who wish to do so have the opportunity to improve their English by taking preparatory education in Turkey. </p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">For More Information: <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/">YÖS Exam in Turkey: Detailed Guide and Preparation Tips</a></p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="labor-force-statistics-2025-current-situation-in-turkey">Labor Force Statistics 2025: Current Situation in Turkey</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">When choosing a university, it is essential to look not only at the popularity of the department, but also at the possibility of finding a job after graduation. At this point, current labor force data tells us a lot.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="employment-rates-according-to-turkstat-data">Employment Rates According to TurkStat Data</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">According to the Turkish Statistical Institute&#8217;s January 2025 <a href="https://www.tuik.gov.tr/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">labor force statistics </a>report:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Number of employed people in Turkey: <strong>32 million 531 thousand people</strong></li>



<li>Employment rate: <strong>49.2%</strong></li>



<li>Unemployment rate: <strong>9.1%</strong></li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">These data show that youth unemployment remains an important issue, despite the effects of a general economic downturn.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="possibilities-of-finding-a-job-after-graduation">Possibilities of Finding a Job After Graduation</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">In Turkey, finding a job after graduating from university varies depending on the department chosen, internships and personal entrepreneurship. However, when we look at the overall picture, the chances are much higher in certain areas.</p>


<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="turkiye-yeni-mezunlar-icin-is-arama-sureci"><strong>The Job Search Process for New Graduates in Turkey</strong></h3>


<p class="wp-block-paragraph">New graduates often start their careers with the following steps:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Get support from university career centers</li>



<li>Participate in career fairs and networking events</li>



<li>To follow job and internship advertisements closely (portals such as <a class="" href="https://www.kariyer.net" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Kariyer.net</a> are very active)</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">For foreign students, finding a job in Turkey can sometimes take several months, so planning before graduation is critical.</p>


<h3 id="popular-industries-and-occupations-for-graduates" class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Popular Industries and Occupations for Graduates</strong></h3>


<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The sectors providing the most employment in Turkey as of 2025 are as follows:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Health Services (especially nursing and doctoring)</li>



<li>Information Technology and Software Development</li>



<li>Finance and Banking</li>



<li>Tourism and Hotel Management</li>



<li>E-Commerce and Logistics</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The demand for graduates with foreign language skills is increasing rapidly, especially in the field of software development.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="departments-with-the-highest-employment-rate-for-international-students">Departments with the highest employment rate for international students</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">For international students studying in Turkey, post-graduation work opportunities are closely linked to their choice of major. Some departments are in high demand both in Turkey and in the global market.</p>


<h3 id="muhendislik-saglik-ve-bilisim-alanlarinda-istihdam-sansi" class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Chance of Employment in Engineering, Health and Informatics</strong></h3>


<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The fastest job finders among international students are usually graduates of the following departments:</p>


<figure class="wp-block-table">
<table class="has-fixed-layout">
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Major</th>
<th>Average Time to Find a Job</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<thead>
<tr>
<td>Software Engineering</td>
<td>4-6 months</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Medicine</td>
<td>2-3 months</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Electrical and Electronic Engineering</td>
<td>5-7 months</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Data Science and Artificial Intelligence</td>
<td>3-5 months</td>
</tr>
</thead>
</table>
</figure>
<h3 id="turkiyede-calisma-izni-almak-adim-adim-rehber" class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Getting a Work Permit in Turkey: Step-by-Step Guide</strong></h3>


<p class="wp-block-paragraph">For international students who want to work in Turkey after graduation, a work permit is required. Here&#8217;s how the process works:</p>



<ol class="wp-block-list">
<li>Contract with an employer in Turkey.</li>



<li>The employer applies to the Ministry of Labor and Social Security.</li>



<li>If the work permit is approved, the residence permit is extended.</li>
</ol>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><a href="https://roadtostudy.com/en/limited-budget-life-strategies-in-turkey/" data-type="post" data-id="5305">Strategies for Living on a Shoestring Budget in Turkey</a> for more information, you can also check out our detailed guide!</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="collaboration-of-universities-in-turkey-with-employers">Collaboration of Universities in Turkey with Employers</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Many universities in Turkey are forging strong ties with employers to help students gain industry experience before graduation. This increases both internship opportunities and chances of direct recruitment.</p>


<h3 id="internship-ve-isyeri-egitim-programlari" class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Internship and Workplace Training Programs</strong></h3>


<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Particularly in state universities and large foundation universities, the following practices are common:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Compulsory summer internships in engineering faculties</li>



<li>Clinical internships in medical schools</li>



<li>Workplace practices in business departments</li>



<li>Erasmus+ internship programs</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">These internship experiences make the transition to working life much easier.</p>


<h3 id="career-centers-and-graduate-support" class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Career Centers and Graduate Support</strong></h3>


<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Career centers are active in most universities. For example:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Ozyeğin University offers one-on-one career counseling to students.</li>



<li>Istanbul Technical University is opening special job placement offices for its graduates.</li>



<li>Bilkent University hosts global career fairs.</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">This support offered by the university significantly increases the chances of finding a job after graduation in Turkey.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="sectoral-employment-trends-for-graduates-in-turkey">Sectoral Employment Trends for Graduates in Turkey</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Which areas will stand out in the Turkish labor market in the next few years?</strong></p>


<h3 id="ulusal-istihdam-stratejisinin-oncelikli-alanlari" class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Priority Areas of the National Employment Strategy</strong></h3>


<p class="wp-block-paragraph">According to the <a href="https://www.csgb.gov.tr/cgm/dokumanlar/ulusal-istihdam-stratejisi/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">National Employment Strategy</a> report published by the Turkish Ministry of Labor and Social Security, the sectors expected to grow the most are:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Information and Communication Technologies</li>



<li>Health Services</li>



<li>Renewable Energy</li>



<li>Logistics and E-commerce</li>



<li>Creative Industries (Game Design, Film, Fashion)</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Graduates who specialize in these fields are significantly more likely to find jobs both in Turkey and Europe.</p>


<h3 id="future-occupations-and-rising-sectors" class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Future Occupations and Emerging Sectors</strong></h3>


<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Among the professions that will be most needed in Turkey after 2025 are the following:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Artificial Intelligence Expert</li>



<li>Renewable Energy Engineer</li>



<li>Data Analyst</li>



<li>Digital Marketing Specialist</li>



<li>Biomedical Engineer</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Making a career plan accordingly can greatly accelerate the process of finding a job after graduation.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Studying in Turkey and pursuing a career after graduation can be one of the best decisions of your life if you take the right steps. Deciding which department you will study and what kind of career you aim for and taking action now will put you in a much stronger position.</p>', '$.wp_published_at', '2026-02-24T07:39:50Z', '$.wp_modified_at', '2026-03-15T18:39:05Z', '$.featured_image', json('{"provider":"external","src":"/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/international-students-in-turkey.webp","alt":"Social life for international students studying at universities in Turkey.","title":"international-students-in-turkey"}')) WHERE "collection" = 'posts' AND "id" = ( SELECT "live_revision_id" FROM "ec_posts" WHERE "deleted_at" IS NULL AND "status" = 'published' AND "locale" = 'en' AND "slug" = 'programs-post-graduation-employment-rates' );
