nt, and apply now!","name":"Turkey Scholarships 2025: Application Guide","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/turkey-scholarships-application-process/#richSnippet","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/turkey-scholarships-application-process/#webpage"},"image":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/turkey-scholarship-program-application-process.webp"},"inLanguage":"en-US","mainEntityOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/turkey-scholarships-application-process/#webpage"}}]}]}', "content_html" = '<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Turkey has become a serious center of attraction in education with the opportunities it offers to international students in recent years. Especially the <strong>Turkey Scholarships Program</strong> offers both a full scholarship and a prestigious education. I remember what I had to go through when I was applying, I made a small date mistake when filling out the first form; luckily I was able to correct it at the last minute. Now I have prepared a step-by-step guide that will make your job easier.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="what-are-turkey-scholarships">What are Turkey Scholarships?</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Turkey Scholarships</strong> is a comprehensive scholarship program funded by the Republic of Turkey that aims to promote academic achievement and international understanding.<br>The program not only provides financial support, but also offers services such as cultural integration support and academic advising to students.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="scope-and-objectives-of-the-program">Scope and Objectives of the Program</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The goal of Turkey Scholarships is to attract successful students from all over the world to Turkey and to raise individuals who will build bridges between their home countries and Turkey after graduation.<br>For more detailed information, you can check our <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/turkiyede-lisans-basvurusu/">Study in Turkey Guide</a>.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="turkey-scholarships-application-requirements">Turkey Scholarships Application Requirements</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Before you apply, you need to meet some basic criteria. Below you can find both the general requirements and the list of documents.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="who-can-apply">Who can apply?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The basic requirements for application are as follows:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Age limit</strong>: Under 21 years of age for bachelor&#8217;s degree and under 30 years of age for master&#8217;s degree.</li>



<li><strong>Academic success</strong>: At least 70% success rate for undergraduate and 75% success rate for master&#8217;s/doctorate.</li>



<li><strong>Health status</strong>: Not having a health problem that prevents getting an education in Turkey.</li>



<li><strong>Nationality</strong>: Not being a citizen of the Republic of Turkey and not studying in Turkey.</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Find these details and more on our <a>YTB Scholarships: You can find out who can apply and how to apply on our page.</a></p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="list-of-required-documents">List of Required Documents</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The main documents you need to upload when applying are:</p>


<figure class="wp-block-table">
<table class="has-fixed-layout">
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Document Name</th>
<th>Description</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>Identity Document or Passport</td>
<td>Must be valid and readable</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Graduation Diploma or Graduation Certificate</td>
<td>Student certificate if you have not yet graduated</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Transcript</td>
<td>Covering all semesters</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Photo</td>
<td>Recently dated, official format</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Motivation Letter</td>
<td>Explain your personal goals and the reason for studying in Turkey</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Letters of Recommendation</td>
<td>Academic or professional references</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</figure>


<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Advice</strong>: Preparing your documents in PDF format and high-quality scans will speed up the application process.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="application-process-stages-and-important-dates">Application Process: Stages and Important Dates</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The application process for Turkey Scholarships is completely online and involves certain steps. If you leave it to the last day like me, you may experience stress like a system crash. So it&#8217;s better to start early!</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="online-application-steps">Online Application Steps</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">When applying, you will follow these steps:</p>



<ol class="wp-block-list">
<li><a href="https://tbbs.turkiyeburslari.gov.tr/" data-type="link" data-id="https://tbbs.turkiyeburslari.gov.tr/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Create registration through the Turkey Scholarships Application System</a>.</li>



<li>Fill out your personal information completely.</li>



<li>Enter detailed information about your education and experience.</li>



<li>Upload your motivation letter and reference letters.</li>



<li>Choose the universities and departments you are interested in.</li>



<li>Save and submit your application.</li>
</ol>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="critical-application-dates">Critical Application Dates</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The application schedule for Turkey Scholarships is generally as follows:</p>


<figure class="wp-block-table">
<table class="has-fixed-layout">
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Date</th>
<th>Stage</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>January-February</td>
<td>Applications received</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>March-April</td>
<td>Pre-evaluation</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>May-July</td>
<td>Interview process</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>August-September</td>
<td>Results announced</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>September-October</td>
<td>Turkey entry and registration</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</figure>


<p class="wp-block-paragraph">I strongly recommend you to follow the official page and <a class="" href="https://roadtostudy.com">RoadtoStudy updates</a> so you don&#8217;t miss the application period.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="how-much-is-turkey-scholarship-monthly">How Much is Turkey Scholarship Monthly?</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Turkey Scholarships not only cover your tuition fees, but also provide you with a regular financial support every month. Honestly, when I received my first scholarship payment, I realized that I could lead a comfortable student life in Istanbul and I felt a great sense of relief.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="expenses-covered-by-the-scholarship">Expenses Covered by the Scholarship</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Here is the support offered by Turkey Scholarships:</p>


<figure class="wp-block-table">
<table class="has-fixed-layout">
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Coverage</th>
<th>Details</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>Monthly Scholarship</td>
<td>Bachelor&#8217;s: 92 USD<br />Master&#8217;s: 132 USD<br />Doctorate: 171 USD</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>University Fee</td>
<td>100% covered</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Health Insurance</td>
<td>Full comprehensive state insurance</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Hostel Accommodation</td>
<td>Free student Dormitory</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Turkish Language Training</td>
<td>1 year free course (if required)</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Flight Ticket</td>
<td>Air tickets provided upon arrival and return after graduation</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</figure>


<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><em>Scholarship payments are made in Turkish Lira and the USD equivalent may vary depending on changes in exchange rates.</em><br></p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">With these supports, living in Turkey becomes quite affordable. I especially recommend you to take a look at the cost of living on <a class="" href="https://roadtostudy.com">Student Budget in Turkey: Average Monthly Cost of Living</a>.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="interview-process-tips-for-success">Interview Process: Tips for Success</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">After going through the application process, getting called for an interview is the next big step. The interview environment is very friendly, but good preparation is essential.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="frequently-asked-questions-in-interview">Frequently Asked Questions in Interview</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">In the interview you will be asked questions such as:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Why do you want to study in Turkey?</li>



<li>What are your career goals for the department you have chosen?</li>



<li>How do you plan to establish a connection between your country and Turkey?</li>



<li>Can you give information about your academic background and projects? </li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The purpose of these questions is to gauge your motivation and determination. The official interview guide can be found <a href="https://www.turkiyeburslari.gov.tr/degerlendirmesecimsureci" target="_blank" rel="noopener">here</a>.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="preparation-tips">Preparation Tips</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Here are a few interview tips:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Know yourself well:</strong> Clearly articulate your goals and why you chose Turkey.</li>



<li><strong>Know about Turkish culture:</strong> Simple cultural references are appreciated by interviewers.</li>



<li><strong>Practice:</strong> Practice a mock interview in front of a mirror or with a friend.</li>



<li><strong>Prepare documents:</strong> Be sure to bring your ID, application form and other documents with you.</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">It is more important to be confident on the day of the interview than anything else, remember that.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="golden-strategies-to-win-a-turkey-scholarship">Golden Strategies to Win a Turkey Scholarship</h2>


<p>I did a lot of research before applying, and I realized that winning a Turkey Scholarship depends not only on GPA, but also on your <strong>application strategy</strong>.</p>


<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="how-to-write-a-motivational-letter">How to Write a Motivational Letter</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The motivational letter is the heart of the application. Here are the points you should pay attention to:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Start with a personal story:</strong> Why did you choose this program? Why are you interested in Turkey? </li>



<li><strong>Explain your goals:</strong> What is your career plan after your studies? </li>



<li><strong>Connect with Turkey:</strong> Show how Turkey&#8217;s opportunities match your goals.</li>



<li><strong>Be original:</strong> Instead of using template sentences, enrich your letter with personal expressions.</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">For a detailed motivation letter: <a class="" href="https://roadtostudy.com">Motivation Letter Writing Guide to Win a Scholarship in Turkey</a>.</p>


<div class="wp-block-spacer" style="height: 22px;" aria-hidden="true"> </div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" />
<div class="wp-block-spacer" style="height: 22px;" aria-hidden="true"> </div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="first-step-to-education-in-turkey-what-to-do-after-the-scholarship">First Step to Education in Turkey: What to do after the Scholarship</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Congratulations! If you have won the Turkey Scholarship, your adventure is just beginning. When I got on the plane for the first time, I was very nervous, but as soon as I landed in Turkey, all my worries were replaced by excitement.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="university-registration-and-visa-process">University Registration and Visa Process</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The process for the winners is as follows:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Registration procedures</strong>: You get an acceptance letter from the university you are assigned to. You register with this document.</li>



<li><strong>Visa application</strong>: To get a student visa for Turkey, you apply to the Turkish Embassy in your home country. Our Student Visa Guide in Turkey can guide you through the visa process.</li>



<li><strong>Housing</strong>: Within the scope of Turkey Scholarships, you stay free of charge in state dormitories. In the first year, this opportunity is definitely a big advantage.</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Advice:</strong> If you prepare your documents in a complete and organized manner, all registration procedures are completed in a few days.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="getting-used-to-life-in-turkey">Getting Used to Life in Turkey</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Student life in Turkey can be both fun and challenging at times.<br>I recommend that you pay attention to the following points during the acclimatization process:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Be open to learning the language:</strong> Although Turkish is difficult at first, you will progress very quickly. Moreover, the Turkish course is free.</li>



<li><strong>Embrace cultural differences:</strong> Hospitality is very strong in Turkey; do not hesitate to meet people.</li>



<li><strong>Plan your budget:</strong> You can easily meet your basic needs with a monthly scholarship, but it is important to control your spending.</li>
</ul>


<div class="wp-block-spacer" style="height: 22px;" aria-hidden="true"> </div>
<h2>Don&#8217;t postpone your dream: Apply for Turkey Scholarships Today!</h2>
<p>If you want to experience an international education, discover a new culture and change your life, <strong>Turkey Scholarships</strong> is a great opportunity for you. Remember, it&#8217;s up to you to take this chance.</p>


